      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(web-fetch): respect NO_PROXY env var when useTrustedEnvProxy is enabled",
        "body": "Closes #93807\n\n## What Problem This Solves\n\nWhen `useTrustedEnvProxy` is enabled, `shouldUseEnvHttpProxyForUrl` returned `true` for all URLs without first checking `matchesNoProxy()`. Local/internal URLs matching NO_PROXY were still routed through the HTTP proxy.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\nAdded `matchesNoProxy()` check in `shouldUseEnvHttpProxyForUrl()` before enabling the proxy. Local addresses matching NO_PROXY now bypass the proxy and connect directly.\n\n## Evidence\n\n```text\n$ npx tsx -e 'import { matchesNoProxy } from \"./src/infra/net/proxy-env.ts\"; ...'\n\nmatchesNoProxy results:\nhttp://localhost:8080    NO_PROXY=localhost             → true  (bypasses proxy)\nhttp://127.0.0.1:9090   NO_PROXY=localhost,127.0.0.1   → true  (bypasses proxy)\nhttp://192.168.1.1:80   NO_PROXY=localhost,192.168.*   → true  (bypasses proxy, wildcard)\nhttp://10.0.0.5:3000    NO_PROXY=localhost,10.0.0.0/8  → true  (bypasses proxy, CIDR)\nhttp://example.com:443  NO_PROXY=localhost             → false (uses env proxy, external)\nhttp://internal.corp:80 NO_PROXY=*.corp,.corp          → true  (bypasses proxy, domain)\n```\n\n**Not tested:** End-to-end with a live proxy server.",
        "branch": "fix/issue-93807-web_fetch-useTrustedEnvProxy-ignores-NO_",
